UYwPd76sSmE.title: Yoga for Core Strength (The New Way) | 20 Minutes | Kino MacGregor
UYwPd76sSmE.description:
In this Yoga for Core Strength practice Kino goes through her most effect (but little known) sequences with you. You'll build strength, increase flexibility, and improve blood flow in your entire body.

After this session you'll feel fresh and strong from head to toe.

You can pair this video Day 1 of our 30-Day Yoga Challenge to stretch out after your workout: https://youtu.be/LhX7VJxkTyU

The sequence uses focused activation, anatomical awareness, and targeted movements to build power and stamina in the core muscles.

An engaged core is very important not just for your yoga practice but in live in general. Come back to this video whenever you need a core strength booster.

Let me know how it went in the comments :-)

t59Gvnumsk0.title: Mountain Pose Tutorial: How To and Health Benefits ( +Tips for Yoga Beginners)
t59Gvnumsk0.description:
Think Mountain Pose is just plain old standing still? Have we got news for you!

Mountain Pose is a fundamental asana and one of the 12 traditional power poses in Sun Salutation A, which you find in both ashtanga and hatha yoga. Standing tall and embodying magnificence in Mountain Pose helps you activates the body and mind, while tapping your inner fire in order to expel dreariness and depression.

When you stand at attention and stillness in Mountain Pose, you are grounding yourself into your body, connecting with your breath, and engaging with all that is Infinite within you. Now what could be cooler than that? ✨🗻✨

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Engage the limitless power of your body, mind, and soul in Mountain Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Mountain Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Tadasana

👏 BENEFITS OF MOUNTAIN POSE: 
1. Strengthens the thighs, knees and ankles
2. Tones the abdomen and glutes
3. Can help Improve posture and relieve sciatica
4. Can aid in kinesthetic awareness and proprioception
5. Great for calming your mind and training your focus

✅ MOUNTAIN POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Stand with your big toes touching, heels slightly apart. Lift and spread your toes wide, rooting down through all four corners of your feet
2. Engage your thighs, lifting your kneecaps slightly (without hyperextending your knees). Draw the energy in toward the midline of your body. Draw your ribs in and tailbone down toward the floor. Pelvis is neutral.
3. Lift your sternum and broaden your collarbones. At the same time, move your shoulders away from your ears, pressing your shoulderblades into your back.
4. With your qrms relaxed by your sides and palms facing forward, bring your chin parallel to the floor, your face and jaw soft.
5. Grow tall from the soles of your feet. Imagine a string pulling you up from your sacrum, all the way up and out through the crown of your head. Stay here for 10 breaths.

localized.description:
Think Mountain Pose is just plain old standing still? Have we got news for you!

Mountain Pose is a fundamental asana and one of the 12 traditional power poses in Sun Salutation A, which you find in both ashtanga and hatha yoga. Standing tall and embodying magnificence in Mountain Pose helps you activates the body and mind, while tapping your inner fire in order to expel dreariness and depression.

When you stand at attention and stillness in Mountain Pose, you are grounding yourself into your body, connecting with your breath, and engaging with all that is Infinite within you. Now what could be cooler than that? ✨🗻✨

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Engage the limitless power of your body, mind, and soul in Mountain Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Mountain Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Tadasana

👏 BENEFITS OF MOUNTAIN POSE: 
1. Strengthens the thighs, knees and ankles
2. Tones the abdomen and glutes
3. Can help Improve posture and relieve sciatica
4. Can aid in kinesthetic awareness and proprioception
5. Great for calming your mind and training your focus

✅ MOUNTAIN POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Stand with your big toes touching, heels slightly apart. Lift and spread your toes wide, rooting down through all four corners of your feet
2. Engage your thighs, lifting your kneecaps slightly (without hyperextending your knees). Draw the energy in toward the midline of your body. Draw your ribs in and tailbone down toward the floor. Pelvis is neutral.
3. Lift your sternum and broaden your collarbones. At the same time, move your shoulders away from your ears, pressing your shoulderblades into your back.
4. With your qrms relaxed by your sides and palms facing forward, bring your chin parallel to the floor, your face and jaw soft.
5. Grow tall from the soles of your feet. Imagine a string pulling you up from your sacrum, all the way up and out through the crown of your head. Stay here for 10 breaths.

poUKMsc9_lU.title: Forearm Plank for Beginners: Yoga Tutorial and Tips (+ Why You Should Do It Everyday)
poUKMsc9_lU.description:
If you're looking to fire up your core, Forearm Plank or is the yoga pose you should be practicing. 💯 Also known as Dolphin Plank or Phalakasana II in Sanskrit, this posture helps tone your core, shoulders, arms, and thighs.

This video teaches you how to properly practice Forearm Plank. When done regularly, this pose helps you build upper body strength and lower body toning, while training you to balance on the forearms.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Awaken and empower your entire body in Forearm Plank!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Forearm Plank
👉 Sanskrit name: Phalakasana II

👏 BENEFITS OF FOREARM PLANK
1. Strengthens your shoulder girdle, arms, and core
2. Activates and tones the glutes, quadriceps, hamstrings, and calves. 
3. Stretches the arches of your feet
4. Prepares your body for arm balances and inversions
5. Relieves mild depression and eases stress

✅ FOREARM PLANK STEP-BY STEP:
1. From Table Top position, bring your forearms to the ground, your shoulders directly above your elbows. Either press the palms into the floor or form a triangle by clasping your hands together.
2. Inhale and step the feet back until you create a straight line in your body from head to heels. With your body parallel to the mat, energetically draw the heels of the feet towards the back of the room.
3. Reach the crown of your head forward, elongating your spine, scooping your tailbone, and engaging the core. Engage the quadriceps by lifting up the kneecaps. This is your Forearm Plank.
4. Stay here for 5 long breaths, or maybe challenge yourself and hold for 60 to 90 seconds.
5. Slowly release the same way you entered.

kN6ITw_AHQQ.title: The Beginner's Guide to Cow Face Pose: Step-By-Step Yoga Tutorial (+5 Health Benefits)
kN6ITw_AHQQ.description:
Cow Face Pose, or Gomukhasana in Sanskrit, is one of the most powerful ways to stretch the chest, upper back, and shoulders, as well as the glutes, hips, and hamstrings.

In the full expression of this yoga pose, the crossed legs are the cow's lips, while the arms—one bent up and one bent down—are the cow's ears.🐮

In this video, you'll learn how to do Cow Face Pose: a powrehouse stretch that opens up your shoulders and pelvis.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Lubricate your lower body and realign your spine in Cow Face Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Cow Face Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Gomukhasana

👏 BENEFITS OF COW FACE POSE:
1. Stretches your shoulders, deltoids, triceps, armpits, and chest
2. Improves your posture by decompressing the lower spine
3. Opens up your hips and activates your ankles
4. Enhances lower body flexibility 
5. Helps release stress, fear, and anxiety

✅ COW FACE POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. From a seated position, place your bent right knee on top of your bent left knee so that your knees are stacked on top of each other, directly in the center of your body. Draw your heels close to your body. Keep both sitz bones glued to the floor so that your hips are leveled.
2. Lift your chest and sit up straight and tall so that your spine is flat.
3. Inhaling, reach your left arm to the sky and bend the left elbow so that your left palm rests on your upper back. Bend your right elbow and move the right hand behind your back, your right palm facing out. Hook your fingers together behind your back so that your hands are between your shoulder blades.
4. Inhale and lift your left elbow towards the sky, as you pull your right elbow towards the ground beneath you. This is your Cow Face Pose.
5. Take 5 deep breaths here, then carefully unwind, and repeat on the opposite side.

R_fkJ8EmzLo.title: How to Practice Eye of the Needle Pose: A Step-By-Step Guide for Beginners (+ Alignment Tips)
R_fkJ8EmzLo.description:
Eye of the Needle Pose or Thread the Needle Variation is an amazing stretch for the pelvis, and the perfect hip opener for those of us with knee or hip issues. ☺️

In this video, you'll learn how to do Eye of the Needle Pose, or Sucirandhrasana in Sanskrit. This posture is effective either for cooling down and moving deeply into the connective tissues of the body, or for warming up and activating the hips and legs.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Open up your hips and pelvis and release your lower back in Eye of the Needle Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Eye of the Needle Pose, Figure 4 Pose, Reverse Pigeon Pose, or Thread the Needle Variation
👉 Sanskrit name: Sucirandhrasana

👏 BENEFITS OF EYE OF THE NEEDLE POSE:
1. Safely yet effectively stretches the hips, particularly the piriformis muscle
2. Releases tension in the hips and lower body
3. Induces relaxation in the knees and lower back
4. Helps prepare the body for deep hip openers like Full Lotus and Pigeon Pose
5. Brings mental ease and clarity

✅ EYE OF THE NEEDLE POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Lying comfortably on the back. Bend your knees and place the soles of your feet hip-distance apart on the mat. Walk your heels in toward your body until you can graze the heels with the fingertips.
2. Cross your right ankle on the left thigh, below your bent knee. Keep the right foot flexed and active, your right toes pointing back toward the right knee. Keep your right foot flexed throughout the duration of the pose to protect the knee joint from injury.
3. Lengthen your tailbone as you maintain the natural curve of the lower back. Pressing your right knee away from your body.
4. Thread your right arm through the space between your legs, interlacing your fingers around the left thigh. Use your arms to gently pull your left leg toward you. Keep your hips square and your head, neck, and shoulders relaxed on the mat. This is your Eye of the Needle.
5. Stay here anywhere from 5 to 25 breaths. To exit this pose, exhale and release the left leg, slowly lowering both feet onto the mat. You can gently rock the knees from side to side to release any tension. Then, come back to center and repeat on the opposite side.

aRSPMMYOXZI.title: Supine Twist for Beginners: A Step-By-Step Yoga Tutorial (+ Holistic Health Benefits)
aRSPMMYOXZI.description:
Supine Twist is a gentle, restorative yoga pose offering countless therapeutic benefits like no other. 😍

Called Jathara Parivartanasana in Sanskrit, this pose massages the abdominal organs, encourages the fresh flow of blood throughout the body, and stimulates the body’s natural detoxification process!

In this video, you'll learn how to do Supine Twist and wring out the knots and tension from deep inside you—just like a sponge!

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Flush out the tightness and  toxins as you relax completely in Supine Twist!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Supine Twist
👉 Sanskrit name: Jathara Parivartanasana

👏 BENEFITS OF SUPINE TWIST:
1. Lengthens and mobilizes your spine
2. Stretches the chest, shoulders, and upper back, as well as the hips and pelvis
3. Massages the internal organs
4. Relaxes, reenergizes, and relieves stress and anxiety
5. Offers a good counterpose to backbends like Bridge or Wheel Pose

✅ SUPINE TWIST STEP-BY STEP:
1. Lying comfortably on the back, bend your knees into your chest and extend your arms out in a “T”, your palms facing the ceiling.
2. Inhaling, lengthen your tailbone down toward the ground. As you exhale, drop both of your bent knees over to the right, gazing over to the left.
3. Keeping your knees and feet close together, press the backs of your shoulderblades down onto the mat. This is your Supine Twist.
4. Stay here for 5-10 breaths, then inhale and come back up to center.
5. On your next exhale, drop your knees to the left, sending your gaze to the right and repeating the twist on the opposite side. After 5-10 breaths, inhale to come back up to center.
6. Wrapping your arms around your legs, gently rock from side to side to release the low back. From here, you can re-center your upper body and extend both legs as you rest in Corpse Pose.

FbbcNo-Au1s.title: How to Do Low Lunge: A Yoga Tutorial  (+ Top Practice Tips for Beginners
FbbcNo-Au1s.description:
Look no further than Low Lunge for a yoga heart and hip opener combo. 😊 Also known as Low Crescent Lunge, or Anjaneyasana in Sanskrit, this pose is named so as it coaxes you into a backbend at your heart center, making you resemble a crescent from the side.

This video teaches you how to do Low Lunge—and helps you work on your flexibility, stability, and posture in the process!

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Create openness throughout your spine and pelvis, while cultivating balance in Low Lunge!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Low Lunge
👉 Sanskrit name: Anjaneyasana

👏 BENEFITS OF LOW LUNGE:
1. Opens up the chest, upper back, and abdomen
2. Strengthens your shoulder girdle and core
3. Stretches tight fip flexors, quadriceps, hamstrings, groin, glutes, and hips
4. Improves posture, lower body flexibilty, and balance
5. Increases energy and helps build confidence

✅ LOW LUNGE STEP-BY STEP:
1. From Downward Dog, exhale and step your right foot forward between your hands.
2. Bring your left knee to the ground, top of the left foot facing down. Stack your right knee directly over the right ankle, right toes pressing firmly down.
3. Relax your arms on either side of your body, shoulders away from the ears. Breathing deeply, shift your weight down into your hips, drawing your tailbone down toward the ground.
4. Bring your hands on your right knee, or touch your fingertips on either side for support. Then, inhale and extend one or both arms up alongside your ears, heart center pointing up and stretching open into a backbend. Core is engaged, shoulders are relaxed, hips are level. This is your Low Lunge.
5. Take 5-10 breaths here. Then, tucking your back toes underneath you, plant your palms onto the mat and make your way back into Downward Dog.
6. Take several breaths in Down Dog, then repeat on the other side.

Ro2mmc6Sk3k.title: The Beginner's Guide to Bridge Pose: A Step-By-Step Yoga Tutorial (+ Holistic Benefits)
Ro2mmc6Sk3k.description:
Eager to get into a yoga backbend? Start with Bridge Pose! 🌉 Called Setu Bandha Sarvangasana in Sanskrit, Bridge Pose is a wonderful entry to the world of backbending, heart-opening yoga poses.

In this video, you'll learn how to do Bridge Pose. You'll create space throughout your front body and spine, build strength in your core, pelvic, and leg muscles, and cultivate renewal from within.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Find release and rejuvenation in your body and mind with Bridge Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Bridge Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Setu Bandha Sarvangasana

👏 BENEFITS OF BRIDGE POSE:
1. Stretches the upper and front body—chest, shoulders, neck, spine, and front legs
2. Strengthens the back body—back, buttocks, and hamstrings
3. Massages the internal organs, helping stimulate digestion and metabolism
4. Calms and energizes the nervous system
5. Promotes physical and mental relaxation

✅ BRIDGE POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Begin lying on your back in a supine position, back of your head and backs of your shoulders are resting on the ground. Avoid moving your head from side to side  when entering, holding, and exiting this pose to protect your neck.
2. Bend your knees, feet hip distance apart, soles flat on the mat, grazing your heels with your fingertips. Root your feet down strongly into the ground.
3. Inhaling, lift your hips up as high as possible, walking your shoulders toward your tailbone, and drawing your tailbone toward your knees. Interlace your fingers and press your forearms and feet strongly into the mat to lift the hips higher.
4. Keep the knees stacked onto your ankles, your feet and thighs hip distance apart and parallel. Lift and draw your chest toward your chin and relax your face. This is your Bridge Pose: take 5 full, deep breaths here.
5. On an exhale, unclasp your hands, draw your shoulders back upward from underneath you, and slowly roll your spine down onto the ground, one vertebra at a time. Bend your knees into your chest and wrap your arms around your legs for a well-deserved hug.

byjUYpre90g.title: Boat Pose for Yoga Beginners: A Step-By-Step  Tutorial (+ Why You Should Do It Everyday)
byjUYpre90g.description:
Boat Pose—Navasana in Sanskrit—is the perfect pose or anyone who is working on their abs, looking to relieve their lower back pain, or searching for an ego boost! 🚢

This video teaches you how to do Boat Pose: a multi-tasking posture that has the ability to improve the strength of your core—as well as the strength of your character.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Learn how to center yourself from inside out with Boat Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Boat Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Navasana

👏 BENEFITS OF BOAT POSE:
1. Strengthens the core muscles, helping ease back pain
2. Stretches and tones the hamstrings and hip flexors
3. Stimulates the digestive, detoxification, and metabolic processes
4. Helps increase self-confidence and emotional intelligence
5. Promotes good posture, balance, and coordination

✅ BOAT POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Sit on your mat, your knees together and bent in front of your chest, feet flat on the floor.
2. Place your hands behind your knees and sit tall, lifting up and forward through the heart. Open the chest and elongate through the crown of your head.
3. Engage your core as you shift your weight to balance on your sitz bones. Lift your shins so they are parallel to the floor.
4. Release your legs and straighten your arms so they are parallel to the floor, palms facing each other or pointing upward.
5. Extend your legs fully and make a "V" with your straight torso and straight legs. This is your Boat Pose. Stay here for 5 full breaths, then slowly release through the same way you entered.

7rcmZGoUnMs.title: Warrior III Tutorial: A Step-By-Step Beginner's Yoga Guide (+ Health Benefits)
7rcmZGoUnMs.description:
In yoga, Warrior III depicts how a warrior dives into battle. As you let go of all fear and charge forward into combat, your form in this pose demands that you keep your energy balanced by extending one leg in the opposite direction.

In this video, you'll learn how to practice Warrior III—Virabhadrasana III in Sanskrit—and improve your core strength, hip flexibility, leg power, and focus in the process!

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Maintain your center as you fight the good fight in Warrior III!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Warrior III
👉 Sanskrit name: Virabhadrasana III

👏 BENEFITS OF WARRIOR III:
1. Sharpens awareness in the feet (Toes, arches)
2. Strengthens the core as well as the ankle and leg muscles that support the knees
3. Stretches and tones the shoulders, chest, and hamstrings
4. Improves balance and posture
5. Helps increase focus and coordination

✅ WARRIOR III STEP-BY STEP:
1. Standing with your feet hip distance apart, inhale to reach your arms up overhead. As you exhale, extend your right leg straight back behind you, shifting your weight onto your left foot and leg.
2. Right foot flexed, toes pointing down, lift the right thigh higher but drop the right hip down to keep it level with the left.
3. Engage the left quadricep to keep the standing leg strong and to avoid locking or hyperextending the left knee. Spread the left toes, drawing up the back arch. Keep both legs as straight as possible without locking the knees.
4. Gazing forward, bring the torso parallel to the floor, shoulders relaxed, core engaged, navel drawn to the spine, neck neutral. Take 5 to 10 breaths here.
5. To exit the pose, use the core and pelvis to slowly bring the right foot back down to meet the left and lift your torso back up to standing. When ready, repeat on the other side.

Pmn_H7z7_DA.title: How to Do Chaturanga: A Quickstart Guide (+Tips for Yoga Beginners)
Pmn_H7z7_DA.description:
Did you know that Chaturanga is yoga's version of the push up? That's right! Called Four-Limbed Staff Pose in English, Chaturanga Dandasana resembles low push up position, but with your hands close by instead of several inches away.

A key part of the yoga Sun Salutation, Chaturanga is called so because your body embodies a stiff, straight piece of wood here, your hands and feet being the four limbs supporting it.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Build your shoulder, bicep, core, and leg strength in Chaturanga!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Four-Limbed Staff Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Chaturanga Dandasana

👏 BENEFITS OF CHATURANGA:
1. Strengthens the shoulders, arms, wrists, back, and core
2. Stretches and tones the leg muscles
3. Improves spinal alignment and posture
4. Warms you up for more vigorous activity
5. Prepares the shoulder girdle and core for arm balances

✅ CHATURANGA STEP-BY STEP:
1. Start in Plank Pose, wrists under the shoulders, heels pushing back, core engaged.
2. Roll forward with your toes, shoulders shifting forward past your wrists, elbows tucked in close to the body.
3. Keep shifting forward so that your arms form a 90-degree angle as you lower toward the floor. Bring the knees down if this feels too much for the arms. Take a few breaths here, activating as much arm and core power as possible. This is your Four-Limbed Staff Pose.
4. Exhale and lower yourself with control onto your stomach, hips, and knees (if you haven't yet).
5. To continue your Sun Salutation, lift up into Cobra Pose or Upward Facing Dog with the next inhale.

localized.title: How to Do Chaturanga: A Quickstart Guide (+Tips for Yoga Beginners)
localized.description:
Did you know that Chaturanga is yoga's version of the push up? That's right! Called Four-Limbed Staff Pose in English, Chaturanga Dandasana resembles low push up position, but with your hands close by instead of several inches away.

A key part of the yoga Sun Salutation, Chaturanga is called so because your body embodies a stiff, straight piece of wood here, your hands and feet being the four limbs supporting it.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Build your shoulder, bicep, core, and leg strength in Chaturanga!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Four-Limbed Staff Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Chaturanga Dandasana

👏 BENEFITS OF CHATURANGA:
1. Strengthens the shoulders, arms, wrists, back, and core
2. Stretches and tones the leg muscles
3. Improves spinal alignment and posture
4. Warms you up for more vigorous activity
5. Prepares the shoulder girdle and core for arm balances

✅ CHATURANGA STEP-BY STEP:
1. Start in Plank Pose, wrists under the shoulders, heels pushing back, core engaged.
2. Roll forward with your toes, shoulders shifting forward past your wrists, elbows tucked in close to the body.
3. Keep shifting forward so that your arms form a 90-degree angle as you lower toward the floor. Bring the knees down if this feels too much for the arms. Take a few breaths here, activating as much arm and core power as possible. This is your Four-Limbed Staff Pose.
4. Exhale and lower yourself with control onto your stomach, hips, and knees (if you haven't yet).
5. To continue your Sun Salutation, lift up into Cobra Pose or Upward Facing Dog with the next inhale.

Pb9Xx7o__os.title: Chair Pose for Beginners: Step-By-Step Yoga Tutorial (+ Health Tips)
Pb9Xx7o__os.description:
Love squats? Then Chair Pose is for you! 😆

Also known as Utkatasana in Sanskrit, Chair Pose is a tough one to get right, but will reward you with loads of leg and glute strength, core toning, hip flexibility, and oodles of character to boot.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Strengthen your entire body with Chair Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Chair Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Utkatasana

👏 BENEFITS OF CHAIR POSE:
1. Strengthens and tones the glutes, quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, and ankles
2. Engages the core and hip flexors 
3. Opens up and stretches the chest and shoulders
4. Combats fallen arches and promotes foot health
5. Trains your concentration, focus, and balance

✅ CHAIR POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Begin standing with your feet hip distance apart and parallel to one another. Spread your toes wide and ground down through all four corners of your feet.
2. On an inhale, sweep your arms overhead, palms facing one another, ears in line with your arms, shoulders relaxed.
3. Exhale bend your knees deeply and shift your hips back as if sitting in a chair. Bring your thighs as close as possible to parallel with the floor, knees hip distance apart, weight on your heels, knees directly over your ankles.
4. Keep your chest lifted and your collarbone broad. Engage your low belly, navel draws into the spine, tailbone points down.
5. Hold the pose for 5 breaths. To come out of the pose, straighten your legs on an inhale, and bring your arms to your sides on an exhale. You may also exhale into Standing Forward Fold before lifting back up to standing.

_UWgcbmaWjY.title: How To Do Upward Dog: A Guide for Yoga Beginners (+ Health Benefits)
_UWgcbmaWjY.description:
An essential pose in the Sun Salutation sequence, Upward Dog is one of the most important and most effective heart openers in yoga. 🐶

Called Urdhva Mukha Svanasana in Sanskrit, Upward Dog creates space in your chest and upper back, activates your spine and vital systems, and strengthens your arms.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Open your heart to courage and confidence with Upward Dog!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Upward Dog Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Urdhva Mukha Svanasana

👏 BENEFITS OF UPWARD DOG:
1. Stretches the chest, shoulders, abdomen, and pelvis
2. Strengthens the wrists, arms, and spine
3. Improves your posture and reverses hunched shoulders
4. Stimulates the abdominal organs
5. Relieves mild depression, fatigue, and sciatica

✅ UPWARD DOG STEP-BY STEP:
1.Start lying on your belly with your legs extended straight behind you, the tops of your feet relaxed on the mat and hip distance apart.
2. Plant your palms beside your ribs, your elbows bent about 90 degrees. On an inhale, press into your palms, straighten your arms and lift your torso, hips, and the tops of your thighs up off the ground. Shoulders are stacked over your wrists, creases of your elbows are facing forward, core is completely engaged.
3. Shoulders are away from your ears and rolling back, pull your chest forward through your upper arms. Chin is in line with the floor. 
4. Keep refining your Upward Dog by firming your thighs and upper outer arms and drawing your navel into your spine.
5. Take 5-10 deep breaths before pushing up to Downward Dog or lowering back down onto the belly.

EX3eZOi-YBU.title: Cat-Cow Pose for Beginners: Yoga Tutorial (+ Health Tips)
EX3eZOi-YBU.description:
Cat-Cow Pose is a wonderful way to warm up the spine at any point in time, on or off your mat. It is so good for loosening up the kinks in your entire back, in fact, that most any yoga class will have it in the beginning! 🐱🐮

If you're looking for a quick pick-me-up and de-stress sesh, you're in luck! This video guides you through Cat-Cow Pose, or Marjaryasana-Bitilasana in Sanskrit, which is perfect for releasing pressure in your back.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Release tension in your spine, energize your vital systems, and calm your mind with Cat-Cow Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Cat-Cow Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Marjaryasana Bitilasana

👏 BENEFITS OF CAT-COW POSE: 

1. Gently mobilizes and eases tension in the spine
2. Stretches the abdomen and hips nicely
3. Stimulates digestion, detoxification, and metabolism
4. Activates posture, balance, and coordination in preparation for more advanced poses
5. Helps calm the mind and create emotional balance

✅ CAT-COW POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Get on all fours on your mat, with your knees hip width apart and your hands directly below your shoulders. Your spine is neutral and your core is engaged here.
2. On an inhale, drop your belly and lift your gaze, all while pointing your tailbone towards the sky in Cow Pose.
3. On an exhale , slowly tuck your chin into your chest, lift your mid-back towards the sky, and scoop your tailbone under in Cat Pose.
4. With your collarbones wide and your core engaged the entire time, do at least four rounds of Cat Cow, then, return to a neutral spine.
5. From here, you can transition into Child's Pose, flow into your next pose, or lift up into Downward Dog and walk to the top of the mat and back to standing,

dO3uCFBCQ-k.title: Warrior Il: Beginner Yoga Tutorial, How To & Tips
dO3uCFBCQ-k.description:
Want focused stability, strength, and power like no other? 😄 Then practice Warrior II! This pose represents the focused attention and warrior ferocity you need to prepare for battle. 

In this video, you’ll learn how to do Warrior II—Virabhadrasana II in Sanskrit. A foundation yoga pose, Warrior II helps build confidence, groundedness, and unwavering concentration.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Free yourself from fear and own your power with Warrior II!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Warrior II
👉 Sanskrit name: Virabhadrasana II

👏 BENEFITS OF WARRIOR II: 
1. Strengthens the shoulders, arms, core, legs, ankles, and feet
2. Stretches the chest and shoulders, as well as the groin, legs, and ankles
3. Stimulates digestion
4. Helps relieve backaches
5. Improves stamina and single-pointed focus

✅ WARRIOR II STEP-BY STEP:
1. Standing at the top of your mat, step your right foot backward about 3-4 feet, heels aligned. Then, pivot to the right to face the long side of the mat.
2. From here, pivot your right foot to the right and your left foot 45 degrees to the right. Bend your right knee directly above your right ankle, pressing firmly into both feet. 
3. Inhaling, extend your arms out through the fingertips as you draw the shoulder blades together. Let the top of the shoulders drop away from the ears. Gaze over your right middle finger.
4. With your shoulders over your hips and your tailbone pointing down, stay here for 5-10 breaths.
5. Inhaling, extend your right leg and exhale to lower your arms. Pivoting left to face the front, step to the top of your mat. Repeat on the other side.

0MYjSbKMVOg.title: Triangle Pose: Step-by-Step Beginner's Tutorial (+ Key Practice Tips)
0MYjSbKMVOg.description:
Need a quick posture fix? Straighten it all out in Triangle Pose. 📐 This standing yoga pose strengthens your core and legs, opens up your hips, and realigns your upper body and spine.

In this video, you’ll learn how to do Triangle Pose—or Trikonasana in Sanskrit—a fundamental yoga pose that combines upper body stretching, core and leg muscle engagement, and body balance.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Start building your flexibility, strength, and balance by practicing and mastering your Triangle Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Triangle Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Trikonasana

👏 BENEFITS OF TRIANGLE POSE: 
1. Stretches your chest, shoulders, and spine
2. Lubricates your hips and groin
3. Engages your core, legs, and ankles
4. Improves your spinal and pelvic alignment
5. Activates your rest and digest mode

✅ TRIANGLE POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Standing at the top of the mat, exhale and step the right foot back 3-4 feet, pivoting to the right to face the long edge of the mat.
2. From here, pivot your right foot to the right and your left foot 45 degrees to the right, both heels aligned. Straighten the legs, keeping a small bend in both knees, pressing firmly on your right big toe.
3. Inhaling, extend both arms all the way through at shoulder height, palms facing down, shoulders soft.
4. Hinging at your right hip, shift your right shoulder 3 inches to the right and bring your right hand down, front body and pelvis facing the long edge of the mat.
5. Place your right hand either on a block outside your right foot, or on your right shin for support.
6. Keeping the core engaged, spin your chest open and reach your left arm up, growing taller through your left fingertips. Keep your head in a neutral position, or gaze toward your left hand if you can.
7. Stay here for 5 breaths. Inhaling, gaze down and press firmly into your feet, then bring yourself back up to standing. Feet are still 3-4 feet apart, facing the long edge of the mat.
8. From here, point your left foot to the left and your right foot 45 degrees to the left. Repeat on this side.

ui1U8wJ3GlE.title: Tree Pose: A Step-by-Step Guide for Yoga Beginners (+ Why You Should Do It Everyday)
ui1U8wJ3GlE.description:
If you're working on both your balance and focus, start with Tree Pose. 🌳 A staple in many types of yoga, Tree Pose is a form of standing meditation, which helps us clear our minds and improve our concentration.

In this video, you’ll learn how to do Tree Pose—or Vrksasana in Sanskrit. As you root to rise and branch out in Tree, you'll find that this pose can put you face-to-face with your ego!

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Build your balance, hip flexibility, and mental strength in Tree Pose!

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Tree Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Vrksasana

👏 BENEFITS OF TREE POSE: 
1. Improves your posture, stability, and balance
2. Opens up the hip flexors, groin, and inner thighs
3. Strengthens your core, leg, ankle, and foot muscles
4. Relieves sciatica pain
5. Enhances your mental focus and self-confidence

✅ TREE POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. From standing, bring your palms together at heart center.
2. Pressing your right foot firmly into the ground, engage your right thigh and core muscles. Slowly lift your left leg and plant the sole of the foot on your right leg, at any point above or below your right knee, but never on your knee.
3. Inhale, grow tall, and gaze at an unmoving spot a few feet in front of you.
4. Try to raise your arms over your head, palms either in prayer or separated but still aligned with your shoulders. Take 5 deep breaths here.
5. Slowly release your arms back to heart center and release the left leg. Repeat on the right side.

92El6s4tPyE.title: How to Do Standing Forward Fold: Yoga Pose Tips and Benefits for Beginners
92El6s4tPyE.description:
New to yoga? Boy, will you love Standing Forward Fold! 🥰 This wonderful pose helps loosen up your hips and lengthen your hamstrings, all while quieting your mind and enhancing your mood.

Called Uttanasana in Sanskrit, Standing Forward Fold also offers a massage to your stomach, liver, and kidney—helping stimulate your internal functions naturally. Seriously, what's not to love? 😂

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Fold deep into your Standing Forward Fold to release tension in your body and decompress your mind. ✨

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Standing Forward Fold
👉 Sanskrit name: Uttanasana

👏 BENEFITS OF STANDING FORWARD FOLD: 
1. As a yoga inversion (where your head is lower than your heart), it enhances your circulation, calms your mind, and relieves anxiety
2. Stretches your hips, hamstrings, and calves
3. Strengthens your thighs and knees
4. Stimulates your digestion, liver, and kidney functions
5. Relieves headaches and fatigue

✅ STANDING FORWARD FOLD STEP-BY STEP:
1. Standing with your feet hip width apart, inhale and grow tall.
2. On an exhale, hinge at the hips and fold forward over the legs, torso draping over the legs.
3. Bend your knees slightly to release tension in the lower back. Head hangs heavy. Either let the arms drape, or hold onto your opposite elbows.You can also bring the fingertips to the ground, or press the palms against the calves.
4. Take 3-5 long breaths here.
5. To come out of this pose, slightly bend the knees, placing the hands on the hips. With the core engaged, inhale, then exhale all the way up to standing.

2KcZN9RKXU0.title: Downward Dog: Tutorial, Tips, & Benefits
2KcZN9RKXU0.description:
Craving some serious stretching, strengthening, and stress relief? 🙋🏼‍♀️🙋🏼‍♂️ Enter Downward Dog. 🐶 This all-levels, quintessential yoga pose combines key muscle engagement with tension release. The result? Total body rejuvenation that makes you stronger and more flexible—basically everything you want out of yoga!

Because it warms, preps, and trains the muscle groups you need to enter essential yoga poses, you'll find Downward Dog—or Adho Mukha Svanasana in Sanskrit—in most all yoga sequences, from beginner to advanced.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍 Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Step right into your Downward Dog to get stronger, stretchier, and most of all, stress-free. ✨

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Downward Dog
👉 Sanskrit name: Adho Mukha Svanasana

👏 BENEFITS OF DOWNWARD DOG: 
1. As a yoga inversion (a pose where your head is positioned lower than the heart) it improves your circulation and calms your nervous system.
2. Releases tension in your neck and shoulders. 
3. Engages and strengthens your core muscles
4. Stretches your spine and lower back
5. Activates your hamstrings and calves

✅ DOWNWARD DOG STEP-BY STEP:
1. Start on your hands and knees, hands slightly in front of your shoulders, knees directly below your hips.
2. From here, spread your fingers wide, actively pushing each finger (and even the webbing between each finger) firmly into the floor.
3. Then, curling your toes under, push your hips high in the air and straighten your arms and legs, coming into an inverted V shape.
4. The goal is to have your back flat with your head between your arms, your legs straight, and your heels touching the floor. Don't worry if these things don't happen all at once—it'll come with regular practice! 
5. Take a minimum of three long inhales and three long exhales here, gazing at your navel if possible. You'll visit this pose often in your yoga classes, so make friends with your Down Dog! 😉

r9ptZumDKJc.title: Cobra Pose Tutorial: Step-by-Step How To & Tips (+ Learn Flexibility Benefits)
r9ptZumDKJc.description:
Want to feel flexy and bendy like a snake? Hello Cobra Pose. 🐍 Great for a stiff upper back and to un-round those shoulders, this is an awesome backbend to learn to relieve neck and back pain - whether you’re beginner or not.

In Cobra pose - or Bhujangasana - in Sanskrit - we imitate a snake lifting its head while working the shoulders, upper back and spine. This video will show you how to do the pose, step-by-step so you can reap the strength and flexibility benefits of this amazing pose.

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Open up our heart, become a bit more vulnerable, and practice being open in the world with Cobra Pose.

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Cobra Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Bhujangasana

👏 BENEFITS OF COBRA POSE: 
1. Increases lower back flexibility
2. Massages the digestive organs 
3. Reduces stress and anxiety
4. Beneficial for neck and back pain
5. Opens up your heart.

✅ CHILD'S POSE STEP-BY STEP:

1. Lie on your stomach and place your forehead on the floor. You can have your feet together, or hip width apart.
2. Place your hands underneath your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body.
3. Draw your shoulder blades back and down, and try to maintain this throughout the pose.
4. Draw your pubic bone towards the floor to stabilize your lower back, and press your feet actively onto the floor.
5. With the next inhale, start lifting your head and chest off the floor. Be mindful of opening the chest, and don't place all of your weight onto your hands. Keep the elbows lightly bent and keep the back muscles working.

vpq8-jcuSbo.title: Child's Pose Tutorial: How To and Stress Relief Benefits ( +Tips for Beginners)
vpq8-jcuSbo.description:
Need a break? Meet Child’s Pose. Simple, stretchy, great to ease lower back pain and it just FEELS good! This awesome resting pose is certainly not *just* for beginners but for yoga practitioners of all levels... after all, everyone needs to rest sometimes.

If you’ve ever taken a yoga class, you’ve probably heard the yoga teacher say… "You can come into Child’s Pose any time you like…." Well you better believe it!

In this video, you’ll learn how to do Child’s Pose - or Balasana in Sanskrit - a yoga pose that thoroughly deserves its reputation as one of the most relaxing ones around. 

👉To learn more beginner's yoga poses, sign up to our free yoga pose library.😍Get step by step tutorials and guidance on how to practice some of the most essential yoga asanas: https://www.doyou.com/programs/beginner-level-poses-i/

Breathe deep and sink into Child's Pose anytime you need to take a break.

*** WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW ***
👉 Pose name: Child's Pose
👉 Sanskrit name: Balasana

👏 BENEFITS OF CHILD'S POSE: 
1. It reminds you that resting is a good thing. 
2. Great for calming the mind.
3. Opens up the hips
4. Elongates the back
5. Stress relief

✅ CHILD'S POSE STEP-BY STEP:
1. Starting on your knees, sit back on your heels.
2. Inhale lengthen through the spine.
3. Exhale as you walk your arms in front of you, bringing your torso down so that you can rest your forehead on the mat.
4. Rest your arms by your sides with your palms facing up near your feet.
5. Breathe deeply for as long as you like. This pose should feel completely relaxing.

The 14 Day Yoga ​Body Challenge is designed to build total body awareness, strength, and flexibility. In just 14 days, 8 minutes a day, you’ll get in-depth insights and step-by-step yoga guides, alignment tips, and flowing yoga sequences to keep your yogi body toned and injury-free throughout your yoga practice. You don’t need to have any yoga experience. Some classes might be physically more challenging, don’t worry if you can’t follow them right away. Yoga is a journey! Your teacher is world-famous yoga legend Briohny Smyth. She brings her passion for living authentically to the mat, inspiring students and yoga teachers to connect with their bodies and stay in true mind-body alignment throughout their yoga journey.

DEpc58Q0Mmg.description:
Sign up for the whole free challenge: https://www.doyou.com/programs/the-30-day-yoga-challenge/

Pigeon pose is one of the best hip-openers around, but can be hard to safely access if your hips are tight to begin with. This class presents different ways to perform this classic pose so you can find the variation that works for you – whether that’s modifying or going one step further.

Tree Pose (Vrksasana) is typically the first balancing posture learned in yoga asana practice, and remains one of the most popular postures among beginners and seasoned yogis alike. 

In this two-minute tutorial, yoga teacher Meagan McCrary shares some of her tips to help you both ground and stabilize your Tree Pose.

UitZOTMCLDI.title: How to Do Pigeon Pose
UitZOTMCLDI.description:
http://www.doyou.com/

Pigeon Pose (Eka Pada Rajakopatasana) is a fantastic hip opener often done toward the end of most yoga classes. However, the pose’s alignment can be a little tricky to understand and isn’t always explained in great detail by the teacher.  

In this very short Pigeon Pose prep tutorial, one of the most frequently asked questions is answered. Where is that front shin and foot supposed to be? You'll also get a few pointers for safely aligning the pose.

Thanks and happy pigeon-ing!


Join the most awesome yoga community online! http://www.doyouyoga.com/community

Ku-t-4Y9Stk.title: How to do Sundial Pose
Ku-t-4Y9Stk.description:
http://www.doyou.com/

An intermediate seated posture, Sundial Pose is a pretty intense shoulder, hip, hamstring and side body opener — that can be a little confusion to approach.

Warm up with five rounds of Sun Salutations and sufficiently stretch your hamstrings and hips, as well as your shoulders and side bodies (Revolved-Head-To-Knee Pose is the perfect precursor to Sundial Pose). Once you’re warm, here’s a 2-minute tutorial on how to do Sun Dial Pose.

Join the most awesome yoga community online! http://www.doyouyoga.com/community

cTBXlsHtSbs.title: How to Use Blocks for a Deeper Backbend
cTBXlsHtSbs.description:
Meagan McCrary offers a quick guide to using yoga blocks for yogis and yoginis with tighter shoulders and/or not enough arm and shoulder strength. For a deeper backbend, try using two blocks at the wall. Wedge the blocks a bit wider than your shoulders into where the floor meets the wall. Then lie on your back with your head between the blocks (crown of the head nearly touching the wall).
 
Place your feet the same as above and the heels of your hands on the blocks. Point both elbow tips up to the ceiling and draw your shoulder blades back. Then press up to the crown of your head and repeat the same actions as above. 

Join the most awesome yoga community online! http://www.doyouyoga.com/community

Please subscribe! http://bit.ly/doyouyoga
